channel.title: .class files!
channel.description:
My .class files are bugged up. Well, I'm trying to edit them with WordPad, but all words at odd! Like, [], etc...
I want to know how I can edit .class files.
Thanks.

item.title: .class files!
item.dc:creator: @Marcuum Marcuum
item.description:
@Marcuum wrote:

[quote=“Muroth, post:4, topic:347815”][quote author=Marcuum link=topic=444196.msg3261450#msg3261450 date=1278531828]

My .class files are bugged up. Well, I’m trying to edit them with WordPad, but all words at odd! Like, [], etc…

I want to know how I can edit .class files.

Thanks.

You don’t need to edit .class files. These are made when you compile .java files. That’s all they are.

Most of the tutorials tell me I need to edit them.
[/quote]

client class = client.java
client.class = client.class[/quote]
Oh lol, your right! Now I know.

Thanks you Muroth, you know how to help!

Read full topic
